1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of guessing a source, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. The paper also introduces a new divergence quantity that measures redundancy, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The problem of guessing under source uncertainty can be seen as a machine learning problem, where the guesser has to learn from the side information to make a good guess. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper identifies good guessing strategies that minimize the supremum redundancy, which can be seen as an algorithmic problem. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper deals with the problem of guessing under source uncertainty, which can be seen as a complexity problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper introduces a new divergence quantity that measures redundancy, which can have applications in cryptography and security.
